name: Good Luck - The Best of Singapore Craft Beers (Bugis - Haji Lane)

reviews.text:
You can call them if they have table before going down . And they do make an effort to get back. But best is just walk in .

Food was pretty good. ambience was also nice , and get to enjoy music from other restaurants. So is still easy to chat with friend .
Attentive Service from Val, Colin , Shane.

Got shoots for Galentine! Really good too with a local flavour .

Great place to chill out after work or catch up with friends .

The food offering is interesting. We went in for some snacks and drinks. They served the wrong beer and gave us the drink for free. We know that the taste is kinda different but wasn’t really paying attention to what was being served when it was brought to us. Wouldn’t have realised it if the staff hadn’t told us.

The beers are amazing and the food is phenomenal. Taste the beers and order food from Fatt Choy Eating House. We ate the Sichuan Dumplings and Iberico Stays skewers and they were so good. Worth the price tag.

Love the experience there, unique decor and very attentive service. Ordered their Dry Laksa, Roxy Laksa, Wagu beef noodles, Spicy oil dumpling, and prawn paste chicken. It was All Good! It is local food done well!
Enjoyed the beer selection. Tried 2 larger and 2 stout.
the food is so good! The satay has its own added flavour of pineapple, nice and juicy meat. Love the carrot cake too, goes so well with beer! Good choices of craft beers on tap!
